                         Thieves
---------------------------------------------------------------------
 
Thieves are the masters of sleight-of-hand.  If they desire something
they don't bother with formalities like asking permission from the
owner or paying for a desired item, they just take it (hopefully
unnoticed).  If they are short on cash they find an unwitting donor
and 'borrow' a few coins from them just to get them by.
 
Thieves tend to be loners or work with others of their class, as
it seems many do not like the thieves' way of making a living.  It
is also not uncommon for there to be bounties placed upon the heads
of thieves, from their disgruntled 'victims'.
 
Because of the need to move silently thieves cannot be encumbered
with heavy armours or huge weapons.  They tend to prefer to wear
lighter armours such as leather, and carry weapons such as daggers
or shortswords.
 
Because thieves work with their hands a lot, dexterity is a prime
requisite for them being able to perform their skills.  Thieves
are also masters in the ability of not being noticed, so they
are very good at blending into the woodwork.
 
Remember to choose your guild carefully, because once chosen, its
a lifetime commitment.
